HEADWORD: Carbide
<hw>Car"bide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Carb</ets>on +
<ets>-ide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A binary compound of
carbon with some other element or radical, in which the carbon plays the
part of a negative; -- formerly termed
<altname>carburet</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

